                        written by CHRSITIAN KARGL

                            Coypright (c)2002


  This is a very simple to use backup program to save your data from your
  hard disc on floppy discs. The documentation is very compact, because
  everybody knows how to use a backup program: simply select the files
  you want to save, click okay, and that's it! Here are more details now:


                            @{"!! Installation  !!" link INSTALL}

                            @{"??  Legal stuff  ??" link LEGAL}

                            @{"   The Main Menu   " link MAINMENU}

                            @{"  Technical Infos  " link TECHNICAL}


  Please contact @{"me" link INFO} if you have any problems, find some errors or just
  want to talk about the source. (pros & cons)

@endnode
@node INSTALL "Power Backup 1.01 »» Installation"
@prev MAIN


   @{HI "Requirements"}
  @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    -> Amiga with hard disc and internal floppy ;-)
    -> Memory: 180K chip, at least 1MB fast (see @{"technical infos" link TECHNICAL})
    -> and Workbench 2.0 (or above) to run that thing...
    -> powerpacker.library V35+ (if you want to compress the data)

   @{HI "Install to hard disc"}
  @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    If you have 186K of free space, copy all files into any drawer you
    want to. (SYS:Tools)

   @{HI "Install to floppy disc"}
  @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
     In case of your boot partition is broken you MUST store a copy
     of the program on a floppy disc. I hope you know how to create a
     bootable disc. After that simply copy the program on the floppy.


@endnode
