    I REPEAT IT FOR YOU: DON'T BACKUP SENSIBLE DATA WITH IT. OF COURSE I
    COULD RECOVER THEM, BUT FLOPPY DISCS ARE ALSO DESTROYABLE. BURN YOUR
    IMPORTANT DATA ON A CD-ROM AND STORE IT AT A SECURE PLACE. PLEASE DO
    ONLY USE MY PROGRAM FOR DATA WHICH YOU CHANGE REGULARY AND THEREFORE
    MUST BE SAVED EVERY 3 OR 4 MONTHS.  PLEASE USE THE 'SIMULATE' OPTION
    IN THE  RESTORE MENU  TO TEST  THE DISCS  THREE TIMES.  IF ALL THREE
    TESTS FAIL REPEAT THE BACKUP.  AFTER THAT YOU SHOULD  REALLY RESTORE
    THE DATA TO A TEMPORARY DIRECTORY  (SYS:EMPTY)  JUST TO BE SURE THAT
    THE DISCS REALLY WORKS. THANKS FOR YOUR ATTETION. HAVE A NICE DAY.


