   Changes from V1.0
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  *) FIXED: if compressed size is larger than original, informations
       for the original file were saved, but with compressed data!
  *) CHANGED: only one reading command for informations instead of four,
       because of strange effects with the file position pointer.
       
   Known Bugs
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
  *) I'm not happy about that, but there is one problem in the backup
     file selection. While development sometimes the program crashes
     with alert $80000003 or $80000004 after the directory tree has
     been generated and you select directories and files. I tried to
     fix it, but it seems to be a problem with AMOS. It didn't happen
     when compiled, and I hope it never happens!

  *) Some (uncompressable) data seems to crash while they are compressed
     with alert number $81000005. But compressing them seperately seem
     to work correctly (with an error message). What the hell...

@endnode

